    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Rather than controlling the elements or transforming the environment, mages of the veil focus on much more subtle magicâ€”blending into their surroundings to watch, observe, and gather secrets, or fading from view completely for the sake of solitude. Most graduates of this college become spies, scouts, or infiltrators.</p>\n<p><strong>Associated School:</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/wizard/arcane-schools/paizo-arcane-schools/classic-arcane-schools/illusion\">Illusion</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong> A mage of the veil must select&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/d/disguise-self\">disguise self</a>&nbsp;as one of his spells known at 1st level.</p>\n<p><strong>Class Skills:</strong> A mage of the veil gains&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/bluff\">Bluff</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/disguise\">Disguise</a>, and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/stealth\">Stealth</a>&nbsp;as class skills.</p>\n<p><strong>Replacement Powers:</strong> This subschool replaces the blinding ray and invisibility field powers of the <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Illusion\">illusion</a>&nbsp;school.</p>",
